  <para>
    <link linkend='MenuItem-OOF.Skeleton.PinNodes'>Pin</link> the
    &nodes; of the currently selected &elems; in the given &skel;.
  </para>
  <para>
    The two parameters, <varname>internal</varname> and
    <varname>boundary</varname> determine exactly which &nodes; will
    be pinned.  If <varname>internal</varname> is
    <userinput>true</userinput>, then &nodes; that are completely
    surrounded by selected &elems; will be pinned.  If
    <varname>boundary</varname> is <userinput>true</userinput>, then
    &nodes; that are only partially surrounded by selected &elems;
    will be pinned.  If both are <userinput>true</userinput>, then all
    &nodes; of the selected &elems; will be pinned. <xref
      linkend="Figure-pinelements"/> illustrates the different
    scenarios.
  </para>
  <figure id="Figure-pinelements">
    <title>Pinning Nodes of Selected Elements</title>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/pinnodes/pineleminternal.png"
	  format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/pinnodes/pineleminternal.eps"
	  format="EPS"/>
      </imageobject>
      <caption>
	<para>
	  &nodes; pinned with
	  <varname>internal</varname>=<userinput>1</userinput> and
	  <varname>boundary</varname>=<userinput>0</userinput>.
	</para>
      </caption>
    </mediaobject>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/pinnodes/pinelemboundary.png"
	  format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/pinnodes/pinelemboundary.eps"
	  format="EPS"/>
      </imageobject>
      <caption>
	<para>
	  &nodes; pinned with
	  <varname>internal</varname>=<userinput>0</userinput> and
	  <varname>boundary</varname>=<userinput>1</userinput>.
	</para>
      </caption>
    </mediaobject>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/pinnodes/pinelemall.png"
	  format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject>
	<imagedata fileref="FIGURES/pinnodes/pinelemall.eps"
	  format="EPS"/>
      </imageobject>
      <caption>
	<para>
	  &nodes; pinned with
	  <varname>internal</varname>=<userinput>1</userinput> and
	  <varname>boundary</varname>=<userinput>1</userinput>.
	</para>
      </caption>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>

